Personal Finance Tracker — Requirements Document (Frontend-Only)

Project Name: Personal Finance Tracker

Platform: Web (mobile-first) — installable as PWA on phone
Theme: Dark mode, modern, sleek, minimal

Hosting: Vercel (frontend only, no backend required)
Data Storage: LocalStorage in browser

1️⃣ Objective

Build a personal finance tracker to:

Track income, expenses, debts, and savings

Follow a monthly budget plan

Visualize progress with graphs and bars

Work offline and store all data locally

2️⃣ Target User

Single user (yourself)

Young professional / developer

Wants mobile-friendly, sleek design

Needs budget control and debt tracking

3️⃣ Core Features
3.1 Dashboard

Show:

Monthly income

Money left today

Remaining budget per category (Food, Lifestyle, Transport, Bills)

Total debts remaining

Savings progress

Visual indicators:

Circular charts for savings progress

Progress bars for debt repayment

3.2 Add Expense

Quick input form:

Category selection

Amount

Optional description

Date (default today)

On save → updates dashboard and LocalStorage

3.3 Debt Tracker

List debts with:

Person name

Total owed

Paid amount

Remaining balance

Visual progress bar per debt

3.4 Savings Tracker

Show:

Total saved this month

Emergency fund progress

Update manually or automatically from remaining budget

3.5 Daily Alerts (Optional)

Show daily remaining budget notification

3.6 History Screen

Scrollable list of all expenses

Color-coded by category

Filter by day/week/month

3.7 Settings

Toggle dark/light mode

Set monthly budgets for each category

Optionally export/import data (JSON backup)

4️⃣ Data Model (LocalStorage)

Income

id

type (Salary / Advance / Side)

amount

date

Expense

id

category (Food / Transport / Bills / Lifestyle / Other)

amount

description

date

Debt

id

person_name

total_amount

paid_amount

remaining_amount

Savings

id

amount_saved

goal_amount

Settings

monthly_budget_per_category

dark_mode_enabled

5️⃣ Technical Stack

Frontend: React (Vite / Next.js)

UI Framework: Tailwind CSS (dark mode first)

Charts: Recharts / Chart.js

State Management: React Context or Zustand

Data Storage: LocalStorage (browser)

Hosting: Vercel (frontend only)

Optional: PWA for mobile install

6️⃣ UX / UI Requirements

Mobile-first design

Dark mode as default

Modern, sleek, minimalist

Rounded cards with subtle shadows

Readable fonts, neon or soft accent colors for highlights

Bottom navigation bar for:

Dashboard

Add Expense

History

Debt Tracker

Settings

7️⃣ App Workflow

User opens app → Dashboard loads data from LocalStorage

User adds income / expense → updates LocalStorage → updates dashboard

User tracks debts → updates LocalStorage

User views savings / progress bars

User can export/import data as JSON if needed

Optional daily alert shows remaining budget

8️⃣ Hosting & Deployment

Deploy React app on Vercel

No backend required

Works offline via PWA

Data persists via LocalStorage